      <hedline>
        <hl1>Toronto Transit</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joanne McLennan letter on June 25 travel article on Toronto notes it is better and safer to use public transit rather than rent auto (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: As an ex-New Yorker, now a resident of Toronto, I thought that ''Toronto: Melting Pot With a Dash of Disco'' (June 25) covered well the major good points of the city. The only thing I would disagree with is renting a car. Toronto has one of the best and safest public transit systems in North America. Moreover, parking is neither plentiful nor cheap. For a mere $7 Canadian a day, the cost of a day pass, a person can travel all over the city and even to such distant parts as the zoo, on the eastern fringe of the city.</p>
        <p>JOANN MCLENNAN  Toronto</p>
      </block>
